#macro FRAME_RATE 60 
#macro TILE_SIZE 16 
#macro CARDINAL_DIR round(direction/90) 
#macro ROOM_START Room1
#macro RESOLUTION_W 480
#macro RESOLUTION_H 270

enum PARADOXES{
    FIRST,
    SECOND,
    THIRD,
    FOURTH,
    TYPE_COUNT
}

/*
My entry for the Bad Ideas Game Jam is a turn-base rogue-like called “Superposition”. In Superposition you play as a cat sent to the “backend of reality” by a group of scientists performing a literal version of the Schrodinger’s cat thought experiment. Other thought experiments and paradoxes have been given physical forms, and you must defeat them all so you can leave. The main gameplay loop involves fighting your way through multiple waves of enemies, getting new weapons, tools, and items along the way, until eventually reaching the boss. The use of thought experiments and paradoxes as gameplay mechanics is the main way this game fits the jam theme of “outside the box”. I had hoped to add more enemies and bosses, but because of time constraints I didn’t have much extra time to do so. Go play my game Superposition for yourself.
ht tps://youtube.com/shorts/JH9MffcI0Oo?feature=share
*/